title: What number is subtracted by 6 to get 9? - Quora

response.answer_text: 15. x - 6 = 9 (starting point based on the information given in the question. x is the number we are trying to find). Adding 6 to both sides of the equation: x -6 +6 = 9 + 6 Of course -6 + 6 is 0 and 9 + 6 is 15. Therefore we get the following: x + 0 = 15 But the 0 does not change the value of x since it is being added, so we can ignore it. So, we get x = 15.
